Currently if trackbacks are disabled and we receive a trackback we get:
{noformat}
2008-08-13 00:53:29,672 http-j2ee.jira.atlassian.com%2F127.0.0.101-8080-Processor46 ERROR [com.atlassian.trackback.TrackbackListenerServlet] com.atlassian.trackback.TrackbackException: Trackback receive disabled
{noformat}

We should change this to INFO.  At the moment, this is just polluting the logs with nothing useful.

Exception thrown while indexing of field that ends with or starts with white-space.

Value being substring'ed is different from the value checking length...  

{code:java}
    public static String getValueForSorting(final String fieldValue)
    {
        if ((!StringUtils.isBlank(fieldValue)) && (fieldValue.length() > MAX_SORT_LENGTH))
        {
            return fieldValue.trim().substring(0, MAX_SORT_LENGTH);
        }
        return fieldValue;
    }
{code}

